      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOMMY TSUNAMI (1) settled back off the inside but went through his gears strongly to find the frame with a 11 length third (23.29) at The Gardens in Mix 2/3. Rates highly and will give a great sight. HEY MICKEY (4) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at his last five runs. Last start finished 3rd in a Mix 1/2/3 on March 2 over 400m at Maitland behind Furious beaten 8 lengths (23.07). Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Must be included in calculations. FIREBALL NIGHT (2) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fourth (16.08) at The Gardens last time. Has a good record at this journey. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Should be in this for a long way. PAPER SHREDDER (8) is always hard to beat when he races here at this trip.",
